article.headline: S.C.-Upstate 80, Kennesaw State 51
article.story: SPARTANSBURG, S.C. -- Nick Schneiders scored 20 points and blocked seven shots to lead South Carolina-Upstate to a dominating 80-51 win over Kennesaw State on Saturday. Josh Chavis added 16 points for the Spartans (9-20, 8-12 Atlantic Sun Conference), who shot 54.5 percent from the field (24-for-44) and held the Owls (7-22, 3-17) to 30.4 percent shooting (17-for-56). Kennesaw State also lost its seventh game in a row and 12 of its last 13 games. S.C.-Upstate never trailed in the contest, pulling ahead 34-21 in the first half on a 3-pointer by Gabor Boros. A dunk off a fastbreak by Chalmers Rogers pushed the Spartans advantage to 53-33 with 10:55 left in the second half and later took their largest margin of the game at 34 points. Jon-Michael Nickerson led the Owls with 15 points, while Spencer Dixon added 14.
